The paper deals with privacy-preserving machine learning on genomic data, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on machine learning techniques and optimization using TensorFlow, which suggests the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Secure Multi-party Computation (MPC) and cryptographic protocols also indicates the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper deals with genomic data, which suggests the category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper deals with collaborative machine learning, which suggests the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
